HIV/AIDS: Kasar Sin ta samu karin mutane 14 cikin 100 da suka kamu da cutar
China ta ba da rahoton cewa adadin Sinawa da ke fama da cutar kanjamau da kanjamau ya karu da kashi 14 cikin ɗari.
Hukumomin kiwon lafiya sun ce mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suka kamu da cutar a ƙasar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai, an samu sabbin mutane 40,000.
A yawancin sababbin cututtuka, ana samun cututtuka ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ba haka yake ba a dā.
A dā, cutar HIV ta yadu da sauri a wasu yankunan ƙasar Sin ta wurin ƙarin jini da ke ɗauke da cutar.
Amma adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV a wannan hanyar ya kusan ƙarewa, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na ƙasar Sin a wani taro da aka yi a lardin Yunnan.
Amma idan aka gwada da wannan lokacin na bara, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS a ƙasar Sin ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000.
Yaduwar cutar kanjamau ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An dakatar da aikata laifukan luwadi a kasar Sin tun shekara ta 1997, amma an ce nuna bambanci ga masu luwadi ya zama ruwan dare gama gari.
Domin ɗabi'ar kasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin ɗari na maza da suke kwana da maza za su auri mace.
Sau da yawa ana samun cututtuka ta hanyar rashin kariya a lokacin jima'i a cikin waɗannan dangantaka.
Tun a shekarar 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar kanjamau ga kowa a kasar a matsayin wani bangare na kokarin magance cutar.
